Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

**1. Route registration (AppShell.xaml.cs):**

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage (e.g., on CollectionView SelectionChanged):**

```csharp
// Approach A — string ID via query string
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. ViewModel receives both approaches in the same method:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load the full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach B — full object passed directly
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?productId=`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | String only | Any object |
| **Serialization** | Values are URI-encoded | No serialization; passed by reference |
| **Use case** | Simple IDs, flags | Complex objects, avoiding a second lookup |
| **Deep-link friendly** | Yes | No (requires in-process navigation) |

Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions, and register the route exactly once in the `AppShell` constructor.
